                                A computer network is a collection of interconnected devices, such as computers,
                                servers, routers, switches, and other hardware components, linked together using wired
                                or wireless communication channels. The primary purpose of a computer network is to
                                enable data sharing, resource sharing, and communication between devices and users.
                                Computer networks have revolutionized how we access information, communicate, and
                                conduct business. They form the backbone of modern technologies, enabling us to stay
